<br>
Ummm... mistmoore, deepest guk... LOTS of undead... hrmm, sounds like heaven for necros to group.<br>
<br>
Mages are just uber dps so dont even go there.<br>
<br>
Druids?  Ya you dont need a cleric.  Druids can heal the right tank (pal/sk) JUST FINE!  Do you &quot;need&quot; a mezzer?  Nope, not if you bring an extra tank, or a buff ranger/rog and a good slower/backuphealer.  I will give LDoN that... the shit is so DAMN EASY (90 minute encounters being beaten easily in 30 with primo groups) its not a Holy Trinity expansion.<br>
<br>
LDoN still sucks, but not because you cant get a group.<br>
<br>
Oh, I forgot to mention the 4th type of mission in my last post.  Mass slaughter.  Gee... anyone ever switch from dwarf to giant faction?  Or vice-versa?  Ya.. we are pretty good at DESTROYING mobs in MASSIVE QUANTITIES that give shit for xp too.  <br>
<br>
LDoN is been there, done that, got the cheeseburger.  However, if you cant get a group in LDoN (the whole damn eq population is there, planes are EMPTY), you pretty much have to suck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xevpeleg>xevpeleg</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.toylodge.com/lib/toylodge/vader.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#330000>(9/12/03 10:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=950.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re</span><hr size=1> Seems to be to be a bit of a mixed bag.  The timer's a bit of a drag since you can't really enjoy yourself rolling through the dungeon or take the time to check anything out... just constantly checking to see your status while you rampage through the zone.  On the other hand, being able to tell the wife that I'll be done in &quot;x&quot; minutes has built enough faction so I can now sleep on the couch instead of in the basement... ;-)<br>
<br>
The loot does seem to suck a bit.  Each dungeon I've been in has dropped all of 1 augmentation gem.  The boss in LFay dropped some wis leggings that were pretty decent, but Druid/Monk/Bst... bleh.  The exp is obviously not PoP style exp, but its good enough more my tastes.<br>
<br>
Like I said, a mixed bag.<br>
