<br>
And yeah, I agree a bit with Dlaritan.  LdoN is more of the same types of romps just with an imposed time limit.  But really, how else could they have done it?  <br>
<br>
I'm not pretending that I'm a game designer, but I don't see how they could have feasibly come up with more POST-POP game content.  Maybe start porting you to another dimension instead of the Plane of Time?  Descend past Time into the depths of Heaven, Hell, Purgatory?  I don't know...it just seems like a brick wall trying to generate more difficult content.<br>
<br>
It's like a building....you can only go so many levels high before you have to start fleshing out the middle parts to stabilize it.<br>
<br>
At any rate, despite the fact that I agree with Dlaritan about the issues he's brought up, I am actually happy with LDoN.  It's a great place to go when I log on and only have 2 or 3 hours to play.  I grab a group of friends, and I don't have to spend half my game time running around doing /camp checks.<br>
<br>
I'll be in LDoN for a while. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=322851"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www3.telus.net/hayzeus/SnowBunny4.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=<br>
