<br>
Raiders in your group will screw you up in any case.  You know that thing they do when their guild calls &quot;Raid&quot; and they just drop everything they're doing and leave?  Quite apart from mucking up your win percentage, they'll also waste a load of your time while you quit the adventure and go looking for a new mezzer or tank.  It's much better not to group with the raid guilders unless you're reasonably sure they are in control of their own time, and very few of them are.  Most of them are slaves to a DKP system and a set of guild rules which are based around old content and hasn't yet caught up to how things are going to be.<br>
<br>
For many of us, raiding was something we did from time to time but we didn't want to make a bloody career out of it.  For many of us, 60-man raids forming up and killing some MoB with an impressive graphic but only two loots - at least one of which will be a PAL/SK 2hs - can only hold your attention for so long before it gets <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>seriously</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> old.<br>
<br>
Well, LDoN gives us another way forward.  If I want to advance my character's gear, I can:  (1) Join some guild with a gay set of rules like &quot;Raiding is mandatory if you are online&quot;, raid 20+ hours a week for the time it takes me to get into the Elemental Planes/Plane of time and sit around farming them, or (2) Put the same amount of time into grouping in the Lost Dungeons of Norrath.<br>
<br>
The difference is that with instanced content I'm not staying up until the small hours of the morning, I'm not bored to death staring at a wall and counting to three in a CH ring, I'm doing things which I'm certain will be advancing my character <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>all the time that I'm playing.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
An expansion with no trains, no camp stealing, no KS'ing, no pre-flagging, no spawn racing, no retards in /ooc, where it's possible to progress towards real upgrades even if you only have a couple of hours to play.  What exactly is the problem?<br>
<br>
Oh sure, it's repetitive, but if you think EQ raiding isn't repetitive then you really shouldn't have a problem with LDoN.<br>
<br>
Look, the thing that always irked me about EQ was the whole attitude of &quot;You have to form a 72-man raid and kill xyz in order to progress further - and by the way, xyz isn't up right now.&quot;  That was pathetic and I'm overjoyed that it's a thing of the past for me.<br>
<br>
But if raids float your boat then stay the hell out of LDoN, nobody's forcing you to go to dungeons! <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=162740">Shadowfrost</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=denamian>Denamian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 222<br> <font color=#330000>(9/13/03 9:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=950.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re</span><hr size=1> With the exception of the leaderboard and the 90 minute time limit pushing group makeup to high dps I like it.  But then Iv'e never been a raider, only going on raids  a few times a month at most. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138587" target="top">Denamian</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
