<br>
Ooze-Covered Pebble of Perfection<br>
HP:20, Mana:20  All Class/Race<br>
Ear, Face, Neck, Shoulder, Back, Range, Primary, Secondary, Finger, Waist <br>
<br>
So for a  whopping 11500 adventure points, players could gain 200 hp/mana if they wished.<br>
<br>
The only other slot &quot;all&quot; augments are mostly +ac, and one or two +mana items that are class specific and go in 5 or so item slots, fortunatly they are cheaper then the above, so if I wanted to I could spend 750 points for 5 augments that would give me 15ac - which is reasonable, but then we're back in the same boat. I guess people are supposed to just save points for the above mentioned item, and get everything else through LDoN raiding ....... may I ask, what is the point of even having a point system again?<br>
