<br>
<br>
I like this expansion a lot. <br>
<br>
Almost every group I've done in LDoN has NOT been the perfect make up.  Very often we go to MM with Cleric/Cleric/Chanter/Shammy/Xdps/Xdps.  Usually cleric #1 is tank/puller.  The last two spots have been filled with anything from 2 warriors, necro/bl, monk/druid...not *real* high DPS groups that have functioned great so far.<br>
<br>
The only thing I don't like is the spam/lag at the camps. Hopefully it will die down as more people get settled into the expansion and don't have to do that quiz at the beginning...it would also help if the maguseseses didn't have 300 lines of text every time someone wants to port somewhere.<br>
<br>
What I really like is that the expansion is for all levels.  If I'm bored with my shammy, I can play in the same areas with my lowish lvl alt..and get her some decent upgrades for free while I'm at it &gt;&lt;<br>
<br>
What does everyone think of the different dungeons? From the leaderboard it looks like most people have been doing Guk/MM (If you havn't done many adventures in a particular zone you can kinda tell how many people have done it by your ranking).  We went to the Oasis (NRo) one last night, and it was kind of annoying. Aggro was weird (similar to CT pulls), and like 99% of the mobs were uncharmable.  There was also an even con (65) earth elemental at the zone in that gave us a good scare, but the rest of the place was DB.<br>
