<br>
Ok, so overall what I´m getting out of this is that the expansion is relatively good, but with the quirks all normal expansions so far have had. It seems SOE does this everytime pretty much... or is it that we´re becoming jaded as we see the strings on the puppets? I mean...<br>
<br>
Shadows of Luclin: Introduced new models (which a lot of people hate), New timesinks and bottlenecks (Ssra races, VT keyparts), New middle-high level mobs (Grieg, THO), New things that were promised but never came or came wayyyy too late (Bazaar, Acrylia), but overall people still fought through the expansion because, hey, is what SOE threw at us, and hey! we got the Nexus now! /yawn.<br>
<br>
PoP: HORRIBLE flagging implementation (sounded sooo good on paper when I first read it), groups were screwed without a slower on the majority of areas, raiding requiring 2 city blocks amount of people and the leadership of (looking on Yahoo) Machiavelli to complete them, exp was good but AA´s were usually crappy, not finished or not worth the effort, SOE´s first real attempt at telling us a story... too bad the story sucked. But hey, we can port to every city now! /yawn.<br>
<br>
Ykesha: The expansion... errr... ¨extension¨ that most people don´t even know it exists. Crappy ugly zones. GIANT zones no one goes to. Broken content (did anyone ever finish up that quest on the ship? Did anyone even want to?) Crappy story (what WAS the story anyway?) amd the add ons like dyes simply alienated those who wanted to look different, after SoL already made all the armor pretty much look the same. But hey, we can be froggies now! /yawn. (Although I still get a kick out of seeing a frog backflip)<br>
<br>
And now LDoN... which you so eloquently dismantled, thanks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So what would have made this expansion better? More styles for the dungeons? (I expected that from the begining and was kinda dissapointed it would only be 5) More race/class combos (then again... why?), More high end content? Melee balance? (don´t even open that can of worms hehe) More variety as far as augmentations and loot rewards go? <br>
<br>
Oh and the reasons why I didn´t include Kunark and Velious above is because I consider Kunark really as part of Original EQ, and Velious the perfect expansion, which was still being played in years after it came out. No one can deny that feeling when they first got to NToV and spent nights there keeling dragons. Or the Big Rush (tm) when your guild first spanked AoW and won... <br>
